label.value: smoothened signaling pathway involved in ventral spinal cord interneuron specification

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a ligand to the transmembrane receptor smoothened in a precursor cell in the ventral spinal cord that contributes to the commitment of the precursor cell to an interneuron fate.

label.value: smoothened signaling pathway involved in spinal cord motor neuron cell fate specification

value.value: The series of molecular signals initiated by binding of a ligand to the transmembrane receptor smoothened in a precursor cell in the spinal cord that contributes to the process of a precursor cell becoming capable of differentiating autonomously into a motor neuron in an environment that is neutral with respect to the developmental pathway.

label.value: oligodendrocyte cell fate specification

value.value: The process in which a cell becomes capable of differentiating autonomously into an oligodendrocyte in an environment that is neutral with respect to the developmental pathway. Upon specification, the cell fate can be reversed.

label.value: oligodendrocyte cell fate commitment

value.value: The process in which the developmental fate of a cell becomes restricted such that it will develop into an oligodendrocyte.

label.value: glial cell fate specification

value.value: The process in which a cell becomes capable of differentiating autonomously into a glial cell in an environment that is neutral with respect to the developmental pathway. Upon specification, the cell fate can be reversed.

label.value: glial cell fate commitment

value.value: The process in which the developmental fate of a cell becomes restricted such that it will develop into a glial cell.

label.value: glial cell development

value.value: The process aimed at the progression of a glial cell over time, from initial commitment of the cell to a specific fate, to the fully functional differentiated cell.

label.value: preganglionic parasympathetic fiber development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of a preganglionic parasympathetic fiber over time, from its formation to the mature structure. A preganglionic parasympathetic fiber is a cholinergic axonal fiber projecting from the CNS to a parasympathetic ganglion.

label.value: postganglionic parasympathetic fiber development

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the postganglionic portion of the parasympathetic fiber over time, from its formation to the mature structure. The parasympathetic fiber is one of the two divisions of the vertebrate autonomic nervous system. Parasympathetic nerves emerge cranially as pre ganglionic fibers from oculomotor, facial, glossopharyngeal and vagus and from the sacral region of the spinal cord. Most neurons are cholinergic and responses are mediated by muscarinic receptors. The parasympathetic system innervates, for example: salivary glands, thoracic and abdominal viscera, bladder and genitalia.

label.value: branchiomotor neuron axon guidance

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone is directed to a specific target site. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: branchiomotor neuron axon guidance in neural tube

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone in the neural tube is directed to a specific target site in the neural tube. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: chemorepulsion of branchiomotor neuron axon in neural tube

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone in the neural tube is directed to a specific target site in the neural tube in response to a repulsive chemical cue. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: chemoattraction of branchiomotor neuron axon in neural tube

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone in the neural tube is directed to a specific target site in the neural tube in response to an attractive chemical cue. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: branchiomotor neuron axon guidance in branchial arch mesenchyme

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone in the branchial arch mesenchyme is directed to a specific target site in the branchial arch mesenchyme. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: chemorepulsion of branchiomotor neuron axon in branchial arch mesenchyme

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone in the branchial arch mesenchyme is directed to a specific target site in the branchial arch mesenchyme in response to a repulsive chemical cue. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: chemoattraction of branchiomotor neuron axon in branchial arch mesenchyme

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone in the branchial arch mesenchyme is directed to a specific target site in the branchial arch mesenchyme in response to an attractive chemical cue. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: chemoattraction of branchiomotor axon

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone is directed to a specific target site in response to an attractive chemical signal. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: chemorepulsion of branchiomotor axon

value.value: The process in which a branchiomotor neuron growth cone is directed to a specific target site in response to a repulsive chemical cue. Branchiomotor neurons are located in the hindbrain and innervate branchial arch-derived muscles that control jaw movements, facial expression, the larynx, and the pharynx.

label.value: thalamus development

value.value: The process in which the thalamus changes over time, from its initial formation to its mature state.

label.value: cerebral cortex cell migration

value.value: The orderly movement of cells from one site to another in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: cerebral cortex regionalization

value.value: The regionalization process that results in the creation of areas within the cerebral cortex that will direct the behavior of cell migration and differentiation as the cortex develops.

label.value: forebrain anterior/posterior pattern specification

value.value: The creation of specific areas of progenitor domains along the anterior-posterior axis of the developing forebrain.

label.value: forebrain dorsal/ventral pattern formation

value.value: The formation of specific regional progenitor domains along the dorsal-ventral axis in the developing forebrain.

label.value: cerebral cortex radially oriented cell migration

value.value: The migration of cells in the developing cerebral cortex in which cells move from the ventricular and/or subventricular zone toward the surface of the brain.

label.value: cerebral cortex tangential migration

value.value: The migration of cells in the cerebral cortex in which cells move orthogonally to the direction of radial migration and do not use radial glial cell processes as substrates for migration.

label.value: cerebral cortex radial glia-guided migration

value.value: The radial migration of neuronal or glial precursor cells along radial glial cells during the development of the cerebral cortex.

label.value: somal translocation

value.value: The radial migration of cells from the ventricular zone that is independent of radial glial cells. Cells extend processes that terminate at the pial surface and follow the processes as they migrate.

label.value: extension of leading cell process to pial surface

value.value: The extension of a long process to the pial surface as a cell leaves the ventricular zone.

label.value: negative regulation of cell adhesion in ventricular zone

value.value: The process that results in the loss of attachments of a cell in the ventricular zone.

label.value: cell movement involved in somal translocation

value.value: The movement of a cell body from the ventricular zone to the pial surface with a concomitant shortening of the process that extends to the pial surface.

label.value: initiation of movement involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The initial stages of cell motility involved in the glial-mediated movement of cells in the developing cerebral cortex.

label.value: motogenic signaling initiating cell movement in cerebral cortex

value.value: The interaction of soluble factors and receptors that result in the movement of cells in the primitive cerebral cortex.

label.value: growth factor signaling initiating cell movement involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: Signaling between growth factors and their receptors that results in the start of cell movement, where this process is involved in glial-mediated radial migration in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: neuronal-glial interaction involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The changes in adhesion between neuronal cells and glial cells as a component of the process of cerebral cortex glial-mediated radial cell migration.

label.value: cell-cell adhesion involved in neuronal-glial interactions involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The interaction between two cells that modulates the association of a neuronal cell and a glial cell involved in glial-mediated radial cell migration in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: cell motility involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The movement of a cell along the process of a radial glial cell involved in cerebral cortex glial-mediated radial migration.

label.value: modulation of microtubule cytoskeleton involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: Rearrangements of the microtubule cytoskeleton that contribute to the movement of cells along radial glial cells as a component of the process of cerebral cortex glial-mediated radial migration.

label.value: extension of a leading process involved in cell motility in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The rearrangements of the microtubule cytoskeleton that result in the extension of a leading process, where this process is involved in the movement of cells along radial glial cells.

label.value: nucleokinesis involved in cell motility in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The microtubule-mediated movement of the nucleus that is required for the movement of cells along radial glial fibers as a component of the process of cerebral cortex glial-mediated radial cell migration.

label.value: layer formation in cerebral cortex

value.value: The detachment of cells from radial glial fibers at the appropriate time when they cease to migrate and form distinct layer in the cerebral cortex.

label.value: extracellular matrix organization in marginal zone involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The process that leads to the deposition of extracellular matrix signals in the marginal zone of the developing cerebral cortex. This extracellular matrix controls the movement of migrating cells. In mammals, the matrix is modified by Cajal-Retzius cells.

label.value: negative regulation of cell-glial cell adhesion involved in cerebral cortex lamination

value.value: The process that results in the release of migrating cells from their interaction with radial glial cells as a component of the process of cerebral cortex glial-mediated radial cell migration.

label.value: negative regulation of cell motility involved in cerebral cortex radial glia guided migration

value.value: The intracellular signaling pathway that results in the cessation of cell movement involved in lamination of the cerebral cortex.

label.value: cerebral cortex tangential migration using cell-cell interactions

value.value: The process in which neurons interact with each other to promote migration along a tangential plane.

label.value: cerebral cortex tangential migration using cell-axon interactions

value.value: The movement of cerebral cortex neuronal precursors tangentially through the cortex using interaction of the migrating cells with axons of other neurons.

label.value: substrate-dependent cerebral cortex tangential migration

value.value: The process where neuronal precursors migrate tangentially in the cerebral cortex, primarily guided through physical cell-cell interactions.

label.value: substrate-independent telencephalic tangential migration

value.value: The process where neuronal precursors migrate tangentially in the telencephalon, primarily guided by interactions that do not require cell-cell contact.

label.value: postnatal olfactory bulb interneuron migration

value.value: The migration of olfactory bulb interneuron precursors in the cerebral cortex that occurs after birth.

label.value: gonadotrophin-releasing hormone neuronal migration to the hypothalamus

value.value: The directional movement of a gonadotrophin-releasing hormone producing neuron from the nasal placode to the hypothalamus.

label.value: oligodendrocyte cell migration from the subpallium to the cortex

value.value: The directed movement of oligodendrocytes from the subpallium to the cerebral cortex during forebrain development.
